DATABASE — NO DESTRUCTIVE OPERATIONS (USER MANDATE)

**Permanent, project-wide rule — not limited to payment plans or any single feature.** It applies to every task and every chat session in this repo.

The user explicitly forbids the agent from damaging or emptying their database.

1. NEVER run or suggest running, unless the user clearly and explicitly asks for that exact destructive action:
   - SQL: `DROP TABLE`, `DROP DATABASE`, `TRUNCATE`, bulk `DELETE` meant to empty a table or wipe data
   - Artisan: `migrate:fresh`, `db:wipe`, `migrate:reset` / `migrate:refresh` when they would drop data (project already blocks some via provider; still do not bypass or work around)
   - Any command or script that deletes tables, truncates, or clears production/local business data

2. Safe by default:
   - Read-only inspection: `SELECT`, counts, `SHOW TABLES`, schema introspection, additive `php artisan migrate` when migrations only add/alter as allowed by PHASE-5
   - Do not run destructive SQL “to test” or “to clean up” without explicit user approval

3. If the user needs data removed, they must state it plainly (e.g. “delete table X”); until then, preserve all tables and rows.
